titlestmt.titleproper: Asian Cultural Council records, Grants, RG 5
A Guide to the Asian Cultural Council records, Grants, RG 5 FA1403

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on 2021-09-02 20:01:06 -0400.

did.unittitle: Asian Cultural Council records, Grants, RG 5

physdesc.extent: Record Group 5 is comprised of boxes 414-949.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The Asian Cultural Council is a publicly supported not for profit 501(c)(3) established in 1980 to support cultural exchange between Asia and the United States. The Council carries forward the mission of the Asian Cultural Program of the JDR 3rd Fund, which had been created by JDR 3rd in 1963 and was officially dissolved in July 1979.

The Asian Cultural Council maintains offices in New York, Hong Kong, Manila (Philippines), Taipei (Taiwan) and Tokyo. ACC affiliation with the Rockefeller Brothers Fund began in 1991, enabling the Council to reduce administrative overhead and devote a larger percentage of its funds directly to grants and program development.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: The Asian Cultural Council records were donated to the RAC in 2010.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: RAC has legal title, copyright and literary rights to the collection in so far as it holds them.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Records Group 5 Grants is arranged primarily alphabetically by subject in the following 21 series. Each series is then further arranged alphabetically by country of origin or record type.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Records are open for research with select materials restricted as noted. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC. Researchers interested in accessing digital media (floppy disks, CDs, DVDs, etc.) or audiovisual material (audio cassettes, VHS, etc.) in this collection must use an access surrogate. The original items may not be accessed because of preservation concerns. To request an access surrogate be made, or if you are unsure if there is an access surrogate, please contact a RAC archivist.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Record Group 5 is comprised of the grant administration files of the Asian Cultural Council, 1958-2007, including such files of the Asian Cultural Program of the JDR Fund which were inherited by the Council following the dissolution of the JDR Fund in 1979.

Grant‚Äêmaking is the core of Asian Cultural Council operations. Through fiscal year 2008, the ACC has provided grant assistance to approximately 6,000 Asian and American artists, scholars and specialists in the arts, awarding approximately 100 grants per year.

Funding is provided in support of the following fields of study: Archaeology; Architecture; Art Education; Art History; Arts Administration; Cinematography; Crafts; Dance; Design; Exhibitions; General Culture; Literature; Museology; Music, Painting; Photography; Sculpture; and Theater.
